getUIText

public java.lang.String getUIText(java.lang.String constant)
Description copied from interface: ResourceGiver

Return a chunk of UI text, usually a single caption or a label, in currently selected language.

If translation in current language (as defined by ResourceGiver.getCurrentLocale()'s #getLanguage() getLanguage() ) is not found translation in #ENGLISH is returned. If translation in #ENGLISH is not found the key-parameter is returned as such.

Specified by:
getUIText in interface ResourceGiver
Parameters:
constant - the key of the UI text to be returned
Returns:
the UI text for given key.

getUIText

public java.lang.String getUIText(java.lang.String key,
                                  java.lang.String... params)
Description copied from interface: ResourceGiver

Return a chunk of UI text, usually a single caption or a label, in currently selected language..
The parameters given are inserted into UI text, replacing all the @0...@n tags, where n is the index of last parameter.

If translation in current language is not found to situation is handled similarly as in ResourceGiver.getUIText(String). If the returned translation does not contain the needed @i-tags no error is raised but the i'th param is simply ignored.

Specified by:
getUIText in interface ResourceGiver
Parameters:
key - the key of the UI text to be returned
params - the parameters inserted in this UI text in correct order.
Returns:
the UI text for given key with parameters inserted.

getTestingExerciseView

public Layout getTestingExerciseView(Executor<?,?> toTest,
                                     GeneralExerciseInfo exerInfo)
Description copied from interface: ResourceGiver
Returns a Component containing all the needed controls for controlling the given Executor. The main use case for this method is to provide a testing view from Editor. The caller must itself know which GeneralExerciseExecutor to instantiate and how to load it with data.

Specified by:
getTestingExerciseView in interface ResourceGiver

getCurrentLocale

public java.util.Locale getCurrentLocale()
Description copied from interface: ResourceGiver

Locale used in the current user session can be used for localization of for example dates (eg. #getDateInstance(int, Locale).

The ResourceGiver.getUIText(String) and related mechanisms should be used for UI-text translations.

Specified by:
getCurrentLocale in interface ResourceGiver
